This paper is about medical image segmentation using deep learning techniques, specifically for liver and tumor extraction from CT scans. The paper proposes a novel 3D hybrid residual attention-aware segmentation method, which is a combination of U-Net architecture, attention modules, and residual learning. This work falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image segmentation. Additionally, it involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the use of attention mechanisms and residual learning suggests that this work may also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) category.
